        "text": "So I think the lowest risk would be to use an existing lexicon\n<https:\/\/lexicon.garden\/browse\/social.colibri>\nthat seems to be the most fleshed out approximation to Slack.\n\nthen try an populate it from Slack webhook. That would only be a one way sync.\n\nWe could use Colibri app to see what it looks like. Colibri is pretty fresh (but <https:\/\/github.com\/colibri-social\/colibri.social|open source>), so nice things like a an app and notification do not exist. But it is open source and the data ends up public so even staying on Slack I think the data sync would be useful for a generic sync API. <@UBN9AFS0N> <@UCUSW7WVD> I was trying to find your code for how you sync from FoC to see how you did it, maybe thats an easier route?",
